FBIS4-61509 "drsov088_a_94033" FBIS-SOV-94-088 Daily Report 5 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Foreign Ministry Urges Rwandan Cease-Fire Foreign Ministry Urges Rwandan Cease-Fire LD0505214794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1236 GMT 5 May 94 LD0505214794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Boris Krivoshey and Aleksandr Krylovich] [Test] Moscow, 5 May -- The Russian side again urgently appeals for the provisional government in Rwanda, the army command, and the Rwandan Patriotic Front to display responsibility for the fate of their country and security in the region, and to cease firing immediately and return to the negotiating table to begin implementing the Arusha agreements. This appeal was made today at a briefing by Director of the Press and Information Department of the Russian Foreign Ministry Grigoriy Karasin. At the current time, he said, Russia is looking at the possibility of assisting with humanitarian aid to the suffering inhabitants of Rwanda.
